MISCELLANEOUS ORDERS

2008-0412. Cincinnati Bar Assn. v. Moeves.

This matter came on for further consideration upon the filing of a motion for an order to appear and show cause filed by relator, Cincinnati Bar Association, on October 19, 2010, requesting the court to issue an order directing respondent to appear and show cause why he should not be found in contempt for his failure to abide by the court’s September 16, 2008 order. The court ordered respondent to respond to relator’s motion. Respondent did not file a response. Accordingly,

It is ordered by the court, sua sponte, that respondent appear in person before this court on January 18, 2011, at 9:00 a.m.
